# Build Tools Prompts

Reference these prompts using: `@prompt-library/workspace-config/build-tools prompt-name`

## Configure TypeScript

**Use when:** Setting up or updating TypeScript configuration

```
Configure tsconfig.json following workspace standards:
1. Use strict mode and modern ES targets (ES2017+)
2. Set up path aliases: @/*, @/lib/*, @/components/*, @/config/*, @/integrations/*, @/services/*, @/infrastructure/*
3. Configure module resolution (bundler for Next.js)
4. Include proper typeRoots (node_modules/@types, lib/types)
5. Exclude: node_modules, supabase, infrastructure/supabase, .next
6. Enable incremental compilation
7. Set jsx to "preserve" for Next.js
8. Enable esModuleInterop and resolveJsonModule
9. Match patterns from existing apps (Feedric/tsconfig.json)

Ensure compatibility with Next.js and workspace build tools.
```

## Configure Next.js

**Use when:** Setting up or updating Next.js configuration

```
Configure next.config.ts following workspace standards:
1. Enable compression and disable poweredByHeader
2. Configure image optimization (formats, deviceSizes, imageSizes)
3. Add security headers (X-Frame-Options, X-Content-Type-Options, etc.)
4. Configure experimental features for performance (optimizePackageImports)
5. Set up proper redirects and rewrites if needed
6. Configure environment variable handling
7. Add performance optimizations
8. Match patterns from existing apps (Feedric/next.config.ts, Markense/next.config.ts)

Ensure all security headers and optimizations are included.
```

## Configure Tailwind

**Use when:** Setting up or updating Tailwind CSS configuration

```
Configure Tailwind CSS following workspace standards:
1. Use design system tokens (CSS variables) for all colors
2. Reference CSS variables in tailwind.config.ts (var(--color-primary), etc.)
3. Configure content paths (app/, components/, lib/ui/, etc.)
4. Set up dark mode (media or class)
5. Extend theme with semantic color tokens (primary, danger, neutral, text, surface, accent, success, warning, info)
6. Ensure all colors reference CSS variables from globals.css
7. Match patterns from existing apps (Feedric/tailwind.config.ts)

Reference .cursor/rules/design-system-tokens.mdc for token standards.
Never use hardcoded Tailwind colors (bg-slate-*, text-gray-*, etc.).
```

## Configure PostCSS

**Use when:** Setting up or updating PostCSS configuration

```
Configure PostCSS following workspace standards:
1. Include Tailwind CSS plugin
2. Include Autoprefixer plugin
3. Set up proper plugin order (Tailwind, then Autoprefixer)
4. Match patterns from existing apps (Feedric/postcss.config.js)

Ensure PostCSS works correctly with Tailwind CSS.
```

## Update Build Config

**Use when:** Updating existing build configurations to match workspace standards

```
Update existing build configurations to match workspace standards:
1. Review current TypeScript config and update to workspace standards
2. Review Next.js config and add missing security headers/optimizations
3. Review Tailwind config and migrate to design system tokens (CSS variables)
4. Update PostCSS config if needed
5. Verify all configurations match patterns from existing apps
6. Test that build still works correctly after updates
7. Document any breaking changes or migration notes

Reference existing apps (Feedric, Markense) for correct patterns.
```
